caption: Another amazing evening at Joe Benny's! I was fortunate enough to get a table inside and enjoy the Bocce Focaccia straight from the oven! Fantastic Italian options and the Best Balls on the block.
Amazing!!! Great food, great people!
Everything from here tastes like heaven. Very polite and welcoming. Hell, I promise you won't feel like ever leaving after eating here

The meatball counter/window continues to deliver amazing food and great service through the challenging circumstances in Baltimore.  I ordered takeout and got the Harrison Hero and Joe Benny (both subs). They are known for the focaccia but everything else here is amazing. Also, you can BUY THE SAUCE!  Thanks to the team for always having a positive and welcoming attitude!
Staff was amazing. It seemed like there was one staff member for each customer.  Food was intricate, colourful, delicious, perfectly plated
Amazing Sicilian-style pizza and an even better atmosphere. *Highly* recommend!
This place is awesome. Not only is the food great, but the staff is outstanding as well. Great pizza, meatballs, and a real "when you're here you're family" vibe. Love it.

This is by far my favorite restaurant; I used to live close enough to come here on a regular basis but have since moved to Richmond, VA and eat here on every return trip.  There is an amazing selection of focaccia "pizzas" from standard toppings to creative ones built by customers.   Be sure to try the meatballs...I used to think that I didn't like meatballs but it turns out when done right they are amazing.   Also, be sure to save room for the cream puffs....bianco Nero is the standard but Joe typically has a seasonal.
Meatball sub !

A recommendation from a friend landed me in this piece of heaven on earth. The food was absolutely delicious and the staff are so friendly. I truly enjoyed the entire experience and I can't wait to go back. Oh we almost left without dessert but we bought it to go. Let me just say this, phenomenal!!!!! Definitely the best balls on the block 👌

Don’t sleep on Joe Benny’s. Best meatballs on the block is an understatement. I ordered the meatballs with pasta (it happened to be penne, but the type of pasta rotates) with burrata mixed into the sauce. It was spectacular. I haven’t had good Italian food in a long time. My wife and I split the sausage pizza which is made on focaccia. It is one of the best pizzas I have ever had. It hit different for all the right reasons. I normally prefer thin crust (NY style) but this made me reconsider things. My wife got the burrata and focaccia bread, and she enjoyed it a lot. Joe chatted with us for a bit which was also really great. How often does a restaurant owner chat with their guests? We will be back for sure. Support your local businesses. Go Stags.
There is no better. It feels like family. Don't be in a hurry and relax!  This style of pizza is the best.

Absolutely loved this restaurant.  The food was high quality and the focaccia and meatballs were excellent.  My wife and daughter were in agreement that if we come back to Baltimore we would have to visit this restaurant again.  Service was outstanding.  Very happy to have stumbled into this restaurant on our first trip to Baltimore.
The best!
I don't remember what pizza was like before Joe Benny's. That is all.
Amazing food and friendly staff. Had a great experience every time whether it was fine in or carry out

After moving to Maryland in June 2019, we found Joe Benny’s while exploring Baltimore and what a find! This’s has now become our go to when we want a night off from cooking. It is where we told old daughter we are expecting, it was now our last meal ‘out’ before delivering our new daughter, and it is the place I can see having future memories made. Whenever friends visiting ask about where to go for pizza, this is where we suggest. It is tiny inside, but so welcoming and really just feels like home. We drive about 30 minutes into Baltimore solely for the focaccia pizza made here and it is very worth it. Definitely give it a try! Fyi- I don’t typically enjoy pizza but my partner is a pizzaholic and we both love the pizza from Joe Benny’s.

Liked this place but we waited a very long time and not sure why. We were there five minutes before they opened. We were the next in line but took five minutes to place order. Once we did i thought it would be only seconds since the meatballs should have been cooked and ready. Instead after ten minutes he said only five minutes more. Took another ten after that. So 25 minutes to put 4 meatballs into a pan and hand it out the window? Really confusing. The meatballs were good and the sauce solid. I just don't understand why it took 25 minutes to get my order when I was there before opening.
Always delicious pizzas.  Meatballs are phenomenal.  Joe Benny and the crew create truly great food and make you feel at home, even during a pandemic.  Stay local!
What’s not to like - the staff is wonderful and personable, the focaccia is amazing, and you won’t find better meatballs anywhere. This is our “go to” to make any bad day much better.
Went here because a friend recommended it. The service was super friendly. The foccacia style pizza was absolutely delicious. I highly recommend stopping by if your near downtown Baltimore.
Try the meatballs, you won't be disappointed with anything on the menu.
It's even better when you can go in and enjoy the true Baltimore ambiance.

Joe Benny's deserves 6 stars.  The food is fantastic and you have to get the flat bread.  Share it, so you leave room for drinks and other food (dessert was great too).  The staff was excellent and if you get a chance, talk with Joe.  You can sense how proud he is of the place and it comes through.  It was an 80's music stream and we loved trying to figure out the band for each song.  This meal finished a great vacation and it was by far the best experience we had all week.  This is a MUST VISIT to Baltimore.
Wonderfully delicious and a total come-as-you-are vibe.
Absolutely love this place. Need to go back and done in once quarantine is over.

This tiny restaurant was delicious! Had the burrata, meatballs and different kinds of personal sicilian pies which they are known for. Loved the food! Friendly staff. If I lived closer, I would be a regular! It's a little place with limited seating. But if you are patient the wait is so worth it. The guy slinging the food aka Joe is awesome. Food is so fresh and amazing. My teen grabbed it off line and so happy we waited. The meatballs are a must, the Ceasar salad is the best oh and the bread oh and pizza. Seriously you cant go wrong!
Always amazing food and such great members of the community. They treat everyone like family. It's always busy, but it is worth the wait.
Good eating worth the drive
A hidden gem.
Incredible meatballs and pizza.
Got the garlicky cheesy focaccia sticks for app. And "The Pete" both were so good!
Great spot especially a first date. The couple next to us got a lot of help from the friendly bartender. Oh yeah, pizza is good too.
Awesome meatballs, love the sauce, and the pizzas are out of this world!
Delicious food and great service. 100% would recommend!
Great food casual atmosphere and friendly staff
Quaint place in Little Italy with great service and a fantastic red sauce.
Best pizza I've had, ever!

I had seen this place several times when I've been walking in the area and I've always been curious - I hadn't heard of a restaurant being called "goldfish" before. It so happens that a friend and I were unable to get a seat at a different restaurant and we wandered over to Kingyo and was told the wait would only be about 15min,
Great pie, friendly service and a cozy atmosphere where everyone is treated like family, and you get the feeling there are lots of regulars. Definitely our new pizza spot!
Everything was delicious, don't sleep on the burrata or the sangria!

Joe's is my favorite and go-to recommendation for anyone looking for neighborhood food in Baltimore. His attention to details in every plate served is noticed by all. Joe will personally check in on guests and if you're lucky enough to grab a seat at the bar, he will chat with you between orders. The atmosphere is cozy, but small. Be prepared for a wait on  a Friday or Saturday prime time. However, the wait is well worth the culinary experience. Favorite menu items: Sloppy Rowe, The Angie (add balls), The Benny Ask if there is any homemade cello - flavors may vary!

(Translated by Google) It's located in a neighborhood and I searched and found it with my colleagues. I was very satisfied with the food I had eaten in America. The atmosphere was good and the staff were good.  (Original) 동네에 위치한 곳인데 검색해보니 맛집이라고 해서 동료들과 찾았습니다. 미국와서 먹은 음식들중 만족도가 매우 높은 곳이였습니다. 분위기도 좋고 직원들도 좋았습니다.

Being from Jersey it's hard to get a good Sicilian slice here in the DMV and finding this little slice of heaven was a blessing. I kept the order simple as a test of the technique and I was impressed. I'll definitely be returning. Service was also great. Location a cute cozy spot in lil Italy great date night option.

A major find in my never-ending search for great Baltimore pizza. $16 seemed a lot, at first, for what I got (3 Sicilian slices in my to-go clamshell). The flavor and quality makes it more than worth it, though. Bangin sauce, crust (their house specialty focaccia style), and perfect toppings (including other house specialty, meatballs). When it comes to B-more pizza, I've got a new #1. I'll be back.
Get the bowl of meatballs and your favorite focaccia pizza. Awesome. Excellent, fair prices.
Absolutely a great place to meet and have a fantastic meal!!  I highly recommend trying this place for a slice of Sicily! (Best meatballs bar none)
Love this place! Some of the best Italian comfort food in Baltimore. Can’t wait until our next visit to Joe Benny’s :)
Great food great service and the best balls!
The best at what they do. Period. 5 stars.
So delicious! Especially the Sloppy Rowe!

Joe Benny’s is my favorite spot in little Italy. Joe & The Gang are always so hospitable and fun to chat with. If you take a date: share the sloppy meatballs, 1 focaccia (or two if you can’t decide on one, you can get a Togo box) and an order of the cream puffs. The second time you go grab that cold cut! Trust me.
The best place for Italian pizza in Maryland!  There's no doubt about it!

Joe Benny’s was an amazing experience. Great costumer service, be ready to wait on a Saturday because there’s no reservations. The meatballs are the best in town, the sauce was delicious. Expect to be greeted by the owner also, he makes sure you are having a great time. The focaccia style pizza was very tasty. Each pizza is personal size, definitely an experience to go there.
The poster child for a great italian spot in Little Italy - great meatballs and if you love focaccia, this is your spot. Joe greets everyone who walks in the door! You feel right at home.

The pizzas are a marvel. I can't seem to get anything that doesnt have burrata and meatballs on it bc these are the show stoppers here. Maybe one day I'll try something else lol. And whether or not youre full, you're just getting the cream puffs anyway. The eponymous sandwich went out in front of me and looked baller. One day I'll just get it to go so I can eat it for lunch the next day bc I'll be too busy eating pizza and meatballs live. Service is stellar.
Amazing pizza. Worth the wait
Best Meatballs in Baltimore!  Joe is great, super nice and funny!
Excellent meatballs
Super friendly place, great scicilian style pie, and very cozy
Beautiful space best server and  Amazing food. Its a place go to with family for diner or lunch...
Teeny tiny and cozy family pizza joint. As authentic as they come. Nothing fancy but outstanding Italian food.

I've been here twice. The fresh toppings is what makes their pizzas come to life. The crust isn't amazing, but it complements the toppings so well that you end up with great slices of mouth watering, lip smacking goodness.

We absolutely loved Nest and have recommended it to all of our friends since our visit. Every aspect of the menu was perfect - perfectly cooked, perfectly presented and perfect service. The staff were so friendly and knowledgeable, even the wine recommendation was spot on. Really enjoyed the evening.

The service was relaxed but attentive. The staff were all friendly and the atmosphere was inviting, though the seating wasn't very comfortable. But as small as the restaurant is, I would imagine they're just going for efficiency with seating.  The food was delicious. We had their famous meatballs as an appetizer and then again on a pizza. However, as good as the food was, it was expensive for the portions given. You're paying the prize of a large pizza for their personal sized pizza. The meatball appetizer runs $2.75 per meatball; they're just regular sized meatballs. But again, the food was very good, and while we didn't leave stuffed, we left content.
This place was amazing. Great atmosphere. Food was delicious. Staff were professional. Great seating Section.
Followed my nose to this place and was the best decision ever.
Excellent!! Real Italian food, not like a chain restaurant.
Love this place!

Down town Baltimore, MD. In the heart of Little Italy district.  Started with a little vino (Planeta Rose):Strawberries, hibiscus and Rhubarb,  slightly tart with a mild sweetness.  No after taste.  One of the other guests had JD &Ginger Beer. Very good also.  Ordered the Bocce Focaccia.  Joe Benney's reminds me of one of the smaller gemstones you find in San Diego  or Oakland.  The place is alive with verbal discourse,  pleasant surprise I may add. I am not disappointed so far. The meatballs with Focaccia bread was amazing enough to savor and went well with the wine. I am confused that another person disparaged the meatballs so flippantly.  I will say I have to strongly disagree with your Assessment!  I really like Joe Benney; he was teasing someone at the Bar about letting a work of art (sandwich) get cold. Great food is meant to be eaten upon its creation. The feast has arrived,  oh my the spiciness is reaching to all of my tastebuds,  they are tingling my palate is a-flutter with the amazing mixture of spices.  One can not do justice in describing the meal other than ,Yes!Yes!  It is taking away my headache and causing me to breathe freely.  The sound around me is reaching an amazing level of long term friends wanting to be heard and hear. This is another little gem to be savoured as one does a fine wine or an amazing fragrance that brings nothing but simple pleasure to one's spirit.  Please visit this amazing little treasure, you might actually enjoy it as I have.

They aren't kidding when they say they have the best balls on the block. Make sure you get there earlier on a weekend, because they will run out of things. This is due to extreme demand. Their drinks are very well priced and quite potent too!

I absolutely love this restaurant. Everyone who works there is funny and kind and just generally good at their jobs. The owner, Joe, will come personally check on how your meal is and say hello. The atmosphere is wonderful, and the food is enough of a draw on it's own. Definitely try the meatballs, they live up to the slogan.
Delicious!

This was recommended to me by my boss when he came to Baltimore one year ago. It was a 10 minute walk from the Inner Harbor. Wow!  Was the food so good. I had the recommended meatballs and Silcilian salad. The best meatballs in Baltimore or anywhere.

I heard about this place all the time. I had to try it before I went to a Orioles game. I had the meatballs. ( best balls in town BY FAR!) Very pleased with Elisa Branden and Joe !!!! Will be back very soon!!!
Delicious focaccia and great meatballs.
Phenomenal local dining spot with wonderfully sassy service. Friendly with just the right amount of spice. You will not be disappointed.
Fantastic food, very nice servers, and an all round great experience.  Will definitely stop by again next time I'm in town.
Delicious food, fun atmosphere, friendly staff.
Not bad at all, delicious and enjoyable!
Staff was friendly and awesome. Food delicious, just a tad bit over priced, but you are in the heart of little Italy.
Excellent spot with great foccacia, cozy ambiance and friendly staff. It's a popular spot so you might have to wait for a table.
Good but can't compare to real Sicilian pie. Had one last week in New Jersey that was outstanding. This was very good but not exactly what I expected.
Pizza but on foccacia bread. Every variation I've had has been delicious!
A gem in Little Italy. Great food!

Incredible food, friendly staff, the owner makes you feel like you're over for Sunday dinner, and intimate seating. The best freaking meatballs and delicious focaccia. Best place to eat in Little Italy ♥️
The best meatballs i have ever had.
Top notch pizza and drinks. Enough said.
Seating is tight but it's well worth it
The best meatballs i have ever had. There mozzarella is on point also. Excellent artisanal focaccia pizza.
Delicious and friendly as always!
Small but fantastic, couldn't have asked for more!

After a day of crowed museums in DC and getting caught up in the rush hour traffic while heading back to Philly, a stop in Baltimore for some food was needed. I'm putting myself out there by saying this, but this place has the best pizza that I've ever had! I'm generally not a pizza lover, but Joe Benny's did not disappoint at all. It's a totally unassuming place for the non-local like myself, but once you have a bite their delicious Sicilian Style pizza and an order of their famous meat balls to start
Great service, better food!  This is the Fiore. It comes with three pieces. I had one and a half and couldn't eat another bite!
Loved everything such a great experience

Love eating here! The food is delicious. The drinks are great. I went with my husband and son. We had the Caesar salad, meatballs, the Pete, and the Angry Ginger. So good. The servers were on top of things, despite it being really busy (and on a Tuesday!!) with a line out the door!  We ordered the July dessert special, cream puffs with vanilla mousse, Nutella drizzle, and a cherry on top. Probably should have ordered two. Love coming here!

Tiny little place. Very popular, so arrive early. Limited menu, but everything is made fresh on site. The pizza and meatballs are the best that can be had anywhere. World class! Beware, the cocktails tend to be on the sweet side. Try to save room for dessert if you can. The profiteroles are awesome.
Meatballs were in the top 5 I've ever had. Waitress was very good.
Food is so delicious and the Sangria is amazing!
The staff is friendly and the food is really good!  recommend at max 4 people since they do not take reservations.
Waited four years for this pizza. Was not disappointed one bit!

When in Baltimore try the Bocce Focaccia, paired with a glass (or two) of vino [Mandrarossa Nero d'Avola] and a mini order of homemade strawberry cheesecake cream puff for dessert. Super delicious! 😋 #JoeBennys

Joe Benny's deserves 6 stars.  The food is fantastic and you have to get the flat bread.  Share it, so you leave room for drinks and other food (dessert was great too).  The staff was excellent and if you get a chance, talk with Joe.  You can sense how proud he is of the place and it comes through.  It was an 80's music stream and we loved trying to figure out the band for each song.  This meal finished a great vacation and it was by far the best experience we had all week.  This is a MUST VISIT to Baltimore.
By far the best meatballs I have ever had. There mozzarella is on point also.
Awesome!
Joe Benny's definitely lives up to all the hype.  Excellent artisanal focaccia pizza.  To die for deserts.  My next visit will be to try the subs.  They look fantastic.  Superb service.
Some of the best pizza in Baltimore and friendly staff and killer desserts.

Small restaurant with very good focaccia pizza.  They have weekday specials on meals and drinks but be mindful they have limited hours.  I will say they are heavy handed with the drinks :)  I strongly suggest giving them a try and I will definitely come back.
Best Italian in little Italy.
Very Nice place
Great Food!   Great Staff! Fun and comfortable.
I really love this place, feels like family. You feel like your in Italy.
Great pizza. Nice atmosphere.

Joe Benny's absolutely stands behind their vibe. The staff is super friendly, and the pizza and meatballs are as good as touted. Also, their phone message made me laugh out loud.  Expect to wait, expect a crowd, and expect to enjoy yourself.

Don't live in the Baltimore area, but was here for a conference and got to make my second visit to Joe Benny's. The first was about two years ago. Took friends with me this time and it was a huge hit with everyone. The focaccia is awesome. The dessert is too. There are only a few tables and if you don't get there when they open at 5, you will have to wait. We arrived at 5:15 and got the last table. Great spot in Little Italy that is walkable --albeit a long walk -- from the Inner Harbor hotels. You won't be disappointed.
Amazing focaccia.   The King Con is where it's at!

In Baltimore for a conference, decided sorta at the last minute to come here for my last dinner in town.  Excellent Sicilian crust pizza, tasty cocktails.  The cream puffs for dessert were divine (they happened to have special pistachio ones when I was there).  Joe and his staff were super friendly.  Overall the most satisfying meal of this trip (most of which were at significantly "fancier" places than this).
Amazing food, great service, friendly folks.  Super excited to get an amazingly delicious menu item that benefits the National Kidney Registry.
Great food, great service. Meatballs and Focaccia with fennel sausage was fantastic. Highly recommend it.
Great service and unbelievable food! Definitely the best balls in town!
Best balls on the block....his puffs aren't bad either.
Such good pizza, ingredient combos to die for. Their famous meatballs might not be worth the price depending on your proclivity to meatballs in the first place
Great food. Genuine Italian! I just wish they had a good rye whiskey, like Sagamore.
Amazing experience
Sweet place, dive bar feel with neighbood best food.

Excellent service and great food.  Courtney was friendly and helpful. Had the "great balls", garlicy-cheeesy-bread, and a fiesty Sicilian pizza. All were great. It's a small place and you may wait but it is worth it.
Great food
Great food. The pizza on foccacio breat is awesome,  the meatballs were very good, the owner/chef was super friendly. If I live in the area I would definitely return to try more menu items.
It's really packed and I understand why. I thought the pizza was exceptional, but just a bit expensive. I will be back, but maybe not as often as I like because of the cost.
Awesome meatballs and really friendly people. I'll go back for sure..
The best service and pizza ever! I will be going again!
Small but homey place for dinner. Can hold big crowds and don't go if you're in a rush. "it's the rules". Very good food!

The drinks are good - they have a good selection of lemoncello cocktails. The place is very small - you will be cramped, and you should not come here with large groups. The atmosphere is cute, though.
I come to Baltimore 3 times a year. For the last 5 I have eaten here at least once per trip. Best Meatballs and the most AMAZING service.
Amazing burrata. And the salad and the focaccia bread. Wish I had more time to enjoy them and their wine list.next time.
Great meal getting one of the last seats at the bar.  Love this place!
I never thought I would love this kind of pizza. I mean... I'm FROM NY! But it was sooo tasty. Too bad I live 90 miles away.
Phenomenal service and food! Meatballs are amazing! Nice neighborhood feel.
Best focaccia in town
Truly the best of Baltimore
Great food, atmosphere and service. Unique style pizza
Excellent Focaccia & meatballs
Expect a wait. Order a pizza with meatballs. The best 2 things they make on one menu item. 3rd best meatball I ever had. (Sorry Joe Benny’s - Grandma Cardoni is #1 and mama C is #2 😘)
Joe Benny's never disappoints...
The pizza here in Joe Benny's are great and it's cheesy.
Wonderful! Like home and I'm from Brooklyn!
Delicious, fresh tasting, flavorful, small, quaint,  superb service
Phenomenal
The photo does not do it justice. Had the pizza with sausage and asked for it to be topped with buratta!  Excellent food and great service.
Great food. Friendly staff

Loved the focaccia pizza, the atmosphere, and the people. Felt right at home, and the pizza was fantastic.  Its neither deep dish nor regular crust pizza, and it's amazing.  The meatballs were also very good. It is small, so a larger party might have some trouble, but it was great for a party of 2.  Highly recommend

I had "The Plain & Simple" which was great except I thought the amount of cheese was kind of excessive and stifled the taste of the tomato sauce underneath. Still very enjoyable and would recommend a visit.
Great food and service. Get the meatballs.
Focaccia pizza!! Rare fine in the city! Great meatballs
Excellent pizza, get there for opening to avoid a wait.

Not your typical restaurant in Little Italy! This place offers modern spins on typical italian dishes. The waitress Courtney was a phenomenal host and provided great suggestions for our order. Great to order solo or to share. Must have the Maria Rita's Bianco e Nero dessert... so good!
Friendly service and great pizza!

The meatballs were amazing and the bread was cooked to perfection but the portions were small and after spending 65 dollars I still left hungry. Great atmosphere, fantastic service and delicious food.
The best sloppy balls I've ever had
Best Balls in Baltimore....meatballs that is!  Foccia Pizza are super.

Any one who gives this place less than  five stars is crazy. I haven't had a bad meal yet. The service is typical for a busy place and the staff is the best and politest I have experienced since moving to Baltimore. Come early, the place fills up fast.

Loved this place. The atmosphere was lively and the servers were incredibly friendly. They warn you up front, saying they will treat you like family and that's exactly what you get. The wait time on a Saturday night was better than expected, and the food/drinks were delicious.
Not sure what's up with these fake positive reviews.. don't be fooled. If you want at least decent sized servings and real Italian food this place is a disappointment
One of the best pizzas I've ever had... And I've been to italy :) must get the meatballs with burrata and the Angie pizza, out of this world good!
Best balls in the street says it all great sauce outstandingly friendly made me want to go back twice

Truly excellent, authentic Italian  food. Fairly small menu done really well. Interesting selection of drinks. Some of the best Italian food I have had in the USA. We were not the only people outside waiting for them to open; like the sign outside says...
They say they have the best balls, but I think it's the sauce. Anyway, fantastic!
Best. Italian. Sub. Ever. Spot of food. A must go to for Baltimore City.
Easily one of the best pizzas I’ve ever had. IN MY LIFE.  Shut up and go.
Delicious food!
Have a great time w Joe n food was out if this world meatballs r the Bomb
One of the best places to eat in Baltimore. Well worth the wait that is often required.
Fantastic! We had the Burrata appetizer and the Kimtuckey pizza! We will definitely be back.
I thought the pizza was good. My group that it was great. The service was great.
Place is small with a long wait. Makes coach class look roomy. But Amazing food.
Unremarkable in every way except for the amount of time it takes to get their toaster oven pizza.

Avoid this place. Measly portions. My wife was mislead by server to believe one pie was plenty for two people. When we received our small styrofoam box it looked like bread you would have for an appetizer, mind you in the same size of a Chinese food to-go box. It was really pathetic.. After speaking with the owner Joe Benny about how me and my wife were disappointed with what happened, he started defending his staff like we were the problem. Also, I'm not just saying this but truly the food is nowhere near as good as some of these reviews claim. The funny part is the owner Joe Benny offered to give us a refund, he took our address down because he made some excuse about his registers. We never received anything. Real stand up guy running this place.. overall horrible experience
Excellent
Amazing meatball dishes

Amazing!  We had the Burrata and the Sammy.  Both were so very good!  There was a wait, but it was well worth it!  We sat at the bar & enjoyed chatting with Joe & some of the frequent patrons.  So happily full, but already planning the next visit - dying to try the Sloppy Rowe & the Pistachio cream puffs.
Sorry to all the little italian grandmothers out there. Joe Benny's has the best meatballs in the entire world.  I have amazing dreams about the Sloppy Row. I hope I have another one tonight 😋
Great food!! The server is very pleasant and she did well serving us! The meatballs appetizer is a must eat!
I was expecting a lot from this place, but I honesty thought the pizza was not great/subpar. And you paid a lot for the food you got. Not sure I'll be back.
A true gem.   The pizza and meatballs are amazing.   You will not regret the visit.

Amazing hospitality at Joe Benny’s. The entire staff is friendly and takes a great deal of pride in their job. They treat you like family whether it’s your first or fiftieth visit. My go to orders are the Sloppy Rowe, Joe Benny, and the Daddio w/ prosciutto. Don’t fill up too much as the cream puffs are incredible for dessert. Make sure you check the chalk board upon entering for the monthly specials.
Very nice place, good service by the owners, great food! A bit slow...expect longer waiting time for the food

It feels like a home away from home. The moment you step through the door, the smell of delicious Italian cooking will surround you. People here are friendly, the mood is relaxed, and the food is honest. Joe will treat you like an old friend and Caleb is more than ready to open your first (and second, and third...they're $3 on Tuesdays) Moretti. Chances are good that you'll see the same cook in the kitchen that prepared your meal the last couple of times you ventured in. Consistency can be expected. Recipes are followed and respected. Start with a Sicilian salad (add arugula) and the Sloppy Rowe Meatballs. Pick whatever focaccia pizza appeals to you-they're all good- and settle in.  I'v never had a meal here that was anything less than spectacular. Joe Benny's is what happens when a person decides to open a restaurant for the sole purpose of sharing good food and good times without any pretense.

You can’t beat this place. My first time visiting and Joe and crew made me feel like a regular. Good pizza. Good drinks. Small place but a gem in the wonderful Little Italy. Make the trip. Enjoy the food. Feel at home.
Best balls in the city. The bread and sauce were amazing.
Best Italian restaurant!
Awesome food. Get there early

Outstanding local Italian restaurant located in Baltimore’s Little Italy neighborhood.  Stopped by on a week day late afternoon with a small group. Location was packed but the staff and other customers graciously worked to make room for our little group at the bar seating.  The Good Excellent Italian. Probably one of the top 5 in terms of the best pizza I’ve ever had the pleasure to consume.  The Bad Very limited seating and if it’s busy be prepared to wait a bit (but it’s worth the wait) There was limited parking in the area which I imagine is only worse on the weekends  Location A bit cramped with about 10 seats at the “bar” right in the entrance and a number of tables packed in behind that deeper in the restaurant. There’s also a few tables out in front. All that said, the atmosphere is excellent. Food A good variety of simple Italian selections primarily focused on Sicilian style pizza and paninis. I tried the pizza and was impressed not only by the taste but also the presentation.  Staff & Service Very friendly staff that seem to take a lot of pride in their jobs. Will return next time I’m in the Baltimore area.
Unexpectedly great

Joe Benny's has a hole in the wall type of feel to it, nothing fancy, but you know the food could be exceptional because of the lack of decor.  Anyways, our waiter, Caleb, was quick and knew the menu well. He suggested that they were known for pizza and meatballs, so that's what we ordered: a Carpi pizza and then the meatballs with the extra cheese sauce.  I think the meatballs were certainly tasty, but maybe a bit small. The sauce that came with it was really good though, excellent when used as dip for the bread that also came with the dish.  The main course, the pizza, was stellar! My wife said it was the best pizza she's ever had! It's got a nice thick and soft crust, with cheese hanging off of every bite. The cheese!! So much cheese!! The cheese is great!! If you like a no frills, straight up cheese and sauce pizza, go for the Carpi!  The only reason we're giving it 4 stars is because the bathroom was a bit dirty. Otherwise, 5 stars all the way!  Maybe they can clean up a bit in the bathroom area.

On Monday 5/19/14 my wife and I went on a date to Joe Benny’s Focacciaria  in Baltimore Maryland’s Little Italy neighborhood.  We had an amazingly fun experience and had to write a review immediately.  We walked in and it was hopping!  The place was being run by 4 staff members buzzing with activity yet we were greeted and welcomed by all of them.  The kitchen bar area was full so my wife and I shared an intimate table in the rear.  Joanne welcomed us and immediately set the table a poured some ice water.  She and my wife began talking and we learned that we had handfuls of friends and coworkers in common (Smalltimore).  We each had an Italian screwdriver – Vodka and blood orange soda.  We took some time with the menu and our drinks.   Joe, the owner/chef came over to introduce himself.  Warm and friendly, he shared his story of his dream to share the food of his family with the city of Baltimore.  His excitement and pride was contagious; we asked if Joe would order for us and serve up “what he does best”, he was more than happy to do so.  First up - The Sicilian Stack – Bright colorful green, red, purple, white of basil, tomato, eggplant, and mozzarella cheese; lightly drizzled with balsamic vinegar and olive oil and a touch of salt.  Like a colorful stack of pancakes you could cut a triangle from the top and get a bite of all of the fresh flavors.  Joe paired that with a glass of a light pino noir a perfect mix of flavor and texture when eaten together with the stack. Joe also served the Burrata – a fresh mozzarella with a firm outside and an internal creamy texture, another excellent pairing with the Pino.  The next course was Mimma’s Meatballs – I’m a carnivore, and I've had ground meats from as many cultures that I can.  I can attest that these are the best meatballs I've ever had.  The perfect blend of pork and beef, firm, yet delicate, even a tiny bit juicy; and the marinara!!  I usually find red sauce boring.  This is the eat with a spoon type of sauce; salty, sweet, tangy and hearty I sopped up every last bit with the excellent house bread. It paired wonderfully with a hefty, jammy Italian red.  For our main course - The Sammy  Focaccia – crispy and soft focaccia with a flavorful lightly oiled texture of garlic and salt topped with more fresh mozzarella and Italian speck which imparted a hint smokey bacon like flavor.  My wife called it quits but I ate every last bite! By this time some space at the kitchen bar opened up, we asked if we could have our after dinner drinks at the bar and the staff welcomed us.  My wife had an Italian Margarita, and I had the Blackeyed ? more finely crafted unique cocktails.  We spent some time hanging out and making friends.  The staff was very busy with a full house yet it didn't feel like they were “working”.  It truly felt like I was a guest in a family’s busy kitchen, and a family that liked each other and wanted to share their food and fun.  Without asking Joe served us what looked like chocolate gelato.  But it wasn't it was something ten times better it was Maria Rita’s Bianco e Nero.  A desert of delicate cream puffs coated in chocolate hazelnut cream.  Amazing! Sometimes I eat at places and I can taste the care in people’s food!  I can taste love and effort at Joe Benny’s.  Baltimore take care Joe Benny’s and his family staff.  They will surely take care of you.
